An overview of the professional creations by Estonian jewellers, designers and smiths. Introduction to the work of different artists, their designs and techniques. Courses and specific techniques used in the specialty are taught at the Estonian Museum of Applied Art and Design.

A historical overview of Estonian jewellery, design and smithery enterprises and their productions. The principles of serial industrial product design; practical courses at different enterprises.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce professional Estonian toreutics.

To introduce the history of the Estonian production of metal objects.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon successful completion of the course, students should: be familiar with the most important Estonian metal artists and their work; be able to distinguish an artist's design from a design presented to a company for production and drawings/measurements made for museological purposes; know the artists' specialty designs.

Upon successful completion of the course, the students should: know the main Estonian toreutic techniques of different historical eras and their output, be able to distinguish an artist's design from a design presented to a company for production and drawings/measurements made for museological purposes; know the design and formation techniques of serial production.
